headline: Tariffs Hitting the Trash Business
summary: Jon Vander Ark, Republic Services President & CEO, tells Open Interest that as tariffs slow down industrial plants, it has created a challenging demand environment for the trash hauler.

headline: Major waste companies spent $659M on M&A in Q2
summary: Companies spent significantly less on M&A than in Q1. WM acquired WB Waste in D.C., while Republic, Waste Connections, GFL and Casella focused on smaller tuck-ins or regional deals.
